grapher in the United States. He established the role at the Minneapolis Journal beginning in 1894 and earlier at the St. Paul and Minneapolis editions of the Pioneer Press."},{"number":2,"category":"military","header":"Spanish-American War correspondent in 1898","body":"In 1898 Edward Augustus Bromley was sent by the Minneapolis Times as war correspondent embedded with the Minnesota troops in the Spanish-American War. He combined news reporting with photography across more than fifty years of Minneapolis journalism and built a personal archive of nearly 1,400 photographs now held by the Hennepin County Library."},{"number":3,"category":"career","header":"Bought seven thousand glass plates from rivals","body":"Across his career Bromley assembled a collection of over seven thousand photographic negatives. He bought five hundred from B.F. Upton in 1878 when Upton relocated to Florida, sixteen hundred from W.H. Illingworth's St. Paul gallery, and the inventories of thirty other photographers. The collection — primarily glass plates — survives at Hennepin County Library."}],"quotes":[],"sources":[{"label":"Edward A. Bromley Photographs collection — Hennepin County Library Special Collections (M/A 0323)","url":"https://archives.hclib.org/repositories/sc/resources/edward_a_bromley_photographs"}],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"slug":"edward-bromley-1849"},"HD3478":{"id":"HD3478","former_ids":[],"is_placeholder":false,"has_descendants_documented":false,"bio":{"first_name":"Edward","middle_name":"St. John","last_name":"Bromley","married_names":[],"gender":"male","display_name":"Edward St. John Bromley"},"birth":{"year":1876,"month":6,"day":17,"city":"Oakdale","county":"Washington","state":"Minnesota","country":"United States"},"baptism":{},"death":{"year":1963,"month":7,"day":22,"county":"Hennepin","state":"Minnesota","country":"United States"},"residence":{},"burial":{"cemetery_id":"CEM168","plot_notes":"Lakewood Cemetery, Minneapolis MN. FindAGrave 170189886."},"cla